FBIS3-49629 "dreeu009aa_94006" FBIS-EEU-94-009 Document Type:Daily Report 13 January 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Further on `Partnership for Peace' Meetings Boross, Klaus on Visegrad Ties LD1201173594 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 1600 GMT 12 Jan 94 LD1201173594 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network Language: Hungarian Article Type:BFN [Text] Hungarian Prime Minister Peter Boross has agreed with the Czech prime minister that there is no need for the Visegrad countries to formally institutionalize their ties. The Hungarian prime minister told this to journalists following talks with Czech Prime Minister Vaclav Klaus in Prague. According to Boross, Hungary is exposed to more dangers than the Czech Republic because of its geographical situation.
